<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-17T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="748" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d748">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18469</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Garrett</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Laredo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-17T17:00:00-06:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Three American soldiers were killed and six wounded and eight Mexicans
                            killed in battle at San Ygnacio on fifteenth instant. Another expedition
                            is being organized, of which Colonel George Guiterrez will be commander
                            and Major Pedro Vena second in command. It is planned to make it larger
                            than the last invading party and it will probably cross or attempt to
                            cross in same region.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>